      "id": "html-tables",
      "moduleId": "html-forms-media",
      "title": "Tables",
      "order": 4,
      "difficulty": "beginner",
      "content": "# Essential to know\n- `<table>` wraps the table\n- `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, `<tfoot>` for sections\n- `<tr>` for rows, `<th>` for headers, `<td>` for data\n- Use tables for tabular data, not layout\n\n---\n\n# Tables\n\nTables display data in rows and columns. They're perfect for structured data like financial reports, schedules, or comparisons.\n\n## Basic Table Structure\n\n```html\n<table>\n  <tr>\n    <th>Name</th>\n    <th>Role</th>\n    <th>Department</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Alice</td>\n    <td>Developer</td>\n    <td>Engineering</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Bob</td>\n    <td>Designer</td>\n    <td>Design</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n```\n\n**Elements:**\n- `<table>` - Container\n- `<tr>` - Table row\n- `<th>` - Table header (bold and centered by default)\n- `<td>` - Table data/cell\n\n## Table Sections\n\nFor better structure and accessibility, use semantic sections:\n\n```html\n<table>\n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Product</th>\n      <th>Price</th>\n      <th>Stock</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  \n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Laptop</td>\n      <td>$999</td>\n      <td>15</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Mouse</td>\n      <td>$29</td>\n      <td>100</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n  \n  <tfoot>\n    <tr>\n      <td><strong>Total Products</strong></td>\n      <td></td>\n      <td><strong>115</strong></td>\n    </tr>\n  </tfoot>\n</table>\n```\n\n**Benefits of sections:**\n- Better accessibility\n- Can style header/footer differently\n- Screen readers can navigate better\n- Can scroll body while keeping header fixed\n\n## Spanning Rows and Columns\n\n### Column Span (colspan)\nMerge cells horizontally:\n\n```html\n<table>\n  <tr>\n    <th colspan=\"2\">Product Information</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Name</td>\n    <td>Price</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n```\n\n### Row Span (rowspan)\nMerge cells vertically:\n\n```html\n<table>\n  <tr>\n    <th>Category</th>\n    <th>Item</th>\n    <th>Price</th>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td rowspan=\"2\">Electronics</td>\n    <td>Phone</td>\n    <td>$699</td>\n  </tr>\n  <tr>\n    <td>Tablet</td>\n    <td>$499</td>\n  </tr>\n</table>\n```\n\n## Complete Table Example\n\n```html\n<table border=\"1\">\n  <caption>Monthly Sales Report - Q4 2024</caption>\n  \n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th scope=\"col\">Month</th>\n      <th scope=\"col\">Revenue</th>\n      <th scope=\"col\">Expenses</th>\n      <th scope=\"col\">Profit</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  \n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <th scope=\"row\">October</th>\n      <td>$50,000</td>\n      <td>$30,000</td>\n      <td>$20,000</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th scope=\"row\">November</th>\n      <td>$65,000</td>\n      <td>$35,000</td>\n      <td>$30,000</td>\n    </tr>\n    <tr>\n      <th scope=\"row\">December</th>\n      <td>$80,000</td>\n      <td>$40,000</td>\n      <td>$40,000</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n  \n  <tfoot>\n    <tr>\n      <th scope=\"row\">Total</th>\n      <td><strong>$195,000</strong></td>\n      <td><strong>$105,000</strong></td>\n      <td><strong>$90,000</strong></td>\n    </tr>\n  </tfoot>\n</table>\n```\n\n**Attributes used:**\n- `scope=\"col\"` - Header applies to column\n- `scope=\"row\"` - Header applies to row\n- `<caption>` - Table title/description\n\n## Table Styling Basics\n\n```html\n<style>\n  table {\n    width: 100%;\n    border-collapse: collapse;\n    margin: 20px 0;\n  }\n  \n  th, td {\n    border: 1px solid #ddd;\n    padding: 12px;\n    text-align: left;\n  }\n  \n  th {\n    background-color: #f5f5f5;\n    font-weight: bold;\n  }\n  \n  tr:nth-child(even) {\n    background-color: #f9f9f9;\n  }\n  \n  tr:hover {\n    background-color: #f1f1f1;\n  }\n  \n  caption {\n    font-size: 1.2em;\n    font-weight: bold;\n    margin-bottom: 10px;\n  }\n</style>\n```\n\n## Responsive Tables\n\nFor mobile, tables can overflow or need horizontal scroll:\n\n```html\n<div style=\"overflow-x: auto;\">\n  <table>\n    <!-- table content -->\n  </table>\n</div>\n```\n\nOr use a responsive pattern:\n```css\n@media (max-width: 600px) {\n  table {\n    display: block;\n    overflow-x: auto;\n    white-space: nowrap;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## When NOT to Use Tables\n\n**❌ Don't use tables for:**\n- Page layout (use CSS Grid/Flexbox instead)\n- Styling lists (use `<ul>` or `<ol>`)\n- Spacing elements\n\n**✅ Use tables for:**\n- Financial data\n- Schedules/timetables\n- Product comparisons\n- Any data that naturally fits in rows and columns\n\n## Quick Reference\n\n```html\n<table>\n  <caption>Table Title</caption>\n  \n  <thead>\n    <tr>\n      <th>Header 1</th>\n      <th>Header 2</th>\n    </tr>\n  </thead>\n  \n  <tbody>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Data 1</td>\n      <td>Data 2</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n  \n  <tfoot>\n    <tr>\n      <td>Footer</td>\n      <td>Data</td>\n    </tr>\n  </tfoot>\n</table>\n```\n\n**Remember:**\n- ✅ Use for tabular data only\n- ✅ Include thead/tbody for structure\n- ✅ Use th for headers with scope attribute\n- ✅ Add captions for context\n- ✅ Style for readability\n- ❌ Don't use for page layout\n- ❌ Don't overuse colspan/rowspan"
    }
  ],
